  "Sanction Details" : "DANNY C. FRYE, WITHOUT ADMITTING OR DENYING THE ALLEGATIONS OF THE DIVISION OF SECURITIES AND RETAIL FRANCHISING THAT HE VIOLATED SECTIONS 13.1-502, 13.1-504 AND 13.1-507 OF THE VIRGINIA SECURITIES ACT, ENTERED INTO A SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT WITH THE VIRGINIA STATE CORPORATION COMMISSION. THE DIVISION ALLEGED THAT MR. FRYE HAD TRANSACTED BUSINESS AS AN UNREGISTERED AGENT AND HAD OFFERED AND SOLD UNREGISTERED SECURITIES IN VIRGINIA. FURTHER THE DIVISION ALLEGED THAT IN OFFERING AND SELLING THESE SECURITIES FRYE HAD MADE MISREPRESENTATIONS AND OMISSIONS OF MATERIAL FACTS. FRYE WAS FINANCIALLY UNABLE TO OFFER RESCISSION TO THE VIRGINIA INVESTORS. AS SETTLEMENT MR. FRYE SENT TO EACH INVESTOR AN EXTENSIVE DISCLOSURE DOCUMENT DESCRIBING THE ISSUER COMPANY (A BROKER-DEALER) FOR WHOM HE HAD SOLD THE SECURITIES, AND OF WHICH HE WAS PRESIDENT. HE ALSO AGREED TO CAUSE THIS BROKER-DEALER, UNITED INVESTORS INTERNATIONAL, TO WITHDRAW ITS BROKER- DEALER APPLICATION IN VIRGINIA FOR A PERIOD OF 24 MONTHS.",
  "Broker Comment" : "UNDER THE ADVICE OF INVESTMENT COUNSEL, I RAISED CAPITAL FOR A BLIND POOL INVESTMENT, WITH WHAT WE WERE LED TO BELIEVE WAS FULL AND ADEQUATE DISCLOSURE.  OUR LEGAL ADVICE WAS IN ERROR AND WHEN WE WERE ADVISED OF SUCH, WE TERMINATED OPERATIONS UNTIL THE QUESTION WAS RESOLVED."
